{"title_page": "Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam", "text_new": "{{short description|2013 film directed by Ponram}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam,\n| image          = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Promotional poster\n| director       = [[Ponram]]\n| producer       = P. Madhan\n| writer         = Ponram [[M. Rajesh]] (dialogues)\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Sivakarthikeyan]]|[[Sathyaraj]]|[[Sri Divya]]|[[Soori (actor)|Soori]]|[[Soundararaja]]}}\n| cinematography = [[Balasubramaniem]]\n| editing        = [[Vivek Harshan]]\n| studio         = [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]]\n| distributor    = Escape Artists Motion Pictures, Khafa Exports (Overseas)\n| released       = {{Film date|2013|09|06|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 158 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| music          = [[D. Imman]]\n| budget         = {{INR}}7.1 crore<ref name=\"sifyvvs\">{{cite web|title=VVS is a blockbuster - The Economics|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vvs-is-a-blockbuster-the-economics-news-tamil-njzj7ugafij.html|work=SIFY|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref>\n| gross          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n'''''Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam''''' ({{trans|The Association of Carefree Youths}}) is a 2013 [[India]]n [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[romantic comedy]] film directed by ''[[Ponram]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/audio-beat-varuthapadatha-vaalibar-sangam-songs-to-lift-your-mood/article4959791.ece |title=Audio Beat: Varuthapadatha Vaalibar Sangam \u2013 Songs to lift your mood |last=S. R. Ashok Kumar |date=27 July 2013 |website=The Hindu |access-date=16 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Varutha-Padatha-Valibar-Sangam-first-look-poster/articleshow/20551411.cms |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam first look poster |work=The Times of India |date=12 June 2013 |accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref> It stars [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Sathyaraj]] and [[Sri Divya]].<ref name=\"sifyvvs1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-gets-ready-news-tamil-ngnk5qdjieg.html |title='Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam' gets ready!|work=Sify|accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-02/news-interviews/38216767_1_sivakarthikeyan-siva-karthikeyan-sathyaraj |title=Sivakarthikeyan and Sathyraj join hands! |work=The Times of India |date=2 April 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> The film was produced by [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]] and has music by [[D. Imman]]. Rajesh wrote the dialogues for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-12-28/news-interviews/36035579_1_siva-karthikeyan-imman-manam-kothi-paravai |title=Imman composes for Siva Karthikeyan's next |work=The Times of India |date=28 December 2012 |accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref> It was filmed in [[Padalur]], [[Theni]], [[Tiruchi]] and [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"sifyvvs1\" /> The film released on 6 September 2013 and performed well at the box office.<ref name=\"Sify top 5\">{{cite web|title=Chennai Box-Office \u2013 Sep 13 to 15|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=15038902&cid=13525926|work=SIFY|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref> The film was remade in Kannada as ''[[Adyaksha]]'' with Sharan playing the lead role and in Telugu as ''[[Current Theega]]'' with [[Manoj Manchu]].<ref>http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/reviews/Movie-review-Sharan-Adyaksha/articleshow/40310678.cms</ref><ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Current-Teega-is-a-Tamil-film-remake/articleshow/42641729.cms</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThe film begins with police arriving at Sivanandi's ([[Sathyaraj]]) house questioning him about killing his daughter Lathapandi ([[Sri Divya]]) because she ran away with the guy she loved. Bosepandi ([[Sivakarthikeyan]]) and Kodi ([[Soori (actor)|Soori]]) are two friends who are the leaders of a group called Varuthapadadha Valibar Sangam. One day, Bosepandi falls in love with Kalyani ([[Bindu Madhavi]]) who is a teacher at a school. Bosepandi writes a love letter for her but wants someone to go give it to her so that's when he finds Lathapandi. Lathapandi gives the letter to her teacher and tricks Bosepandi into believing many things.\n\nSivanandi fixes a marriage for Lathapandi but she is not willing to marry because she is very young and she wants to study further. Despite her attempts, nothing stops her marriage. Her marriage was posted on a billboard and Bosepandi and Kodi decide to stop it. They go to the police station and threaten the police that they will go to the commissioner. The police talks to Sivanandi and makes him stop the marriage. One day, Lathapandi delivers the news to Bosepandi that Kalyani is getting married. He decides to move on in life, so he arranges for a Dindigul programme to happen in his area. He sees Lathapandi in a sari and immediately falls in love with her. The same night, the police reveals to Sivanandi that the person who stopped Lathapandi's marriage was Bosepandi.\n\nA day later he tells her about his love for her but she ignores him and says no. Bosepandi walks away listening to a sad song when a gang comes and bashes him. He later finds out that it was Sivanandi's gang who hit him. So Bosepandi and Kodi decide to steal what Sivanandi considers his 'soul' and that is his gun. Bosepandi and Kodi steal the gun and run away and cause a lot of trouble. Bosepandi then tells Lathapandi that he will return the gun if she comes to their friends marriage and so he returns the gun without anyone knowing. Lathapandi in return, goes to that marriage and takes lots of photos with Bosepandi. Her mother warns her that this is not correct and she should stop it. Sivanandi's cow falls into a well when he goes out of town so Bosepandi helps to get it out. That night he stays with Lathapandi in her house and they see Sivanandi sleepwalking. After that, they wake up in the morning and they see Sivanandi walking again. This time he is awake but Bosepandi thinks he's sleepwalking again and so he tells Sivanandi about liking his daughter. Once he finds out that he is indeed awake, he runs out of that house.\n\nSivanandi then makes Lathapandi promise that she will only marry the guy who Sivanandi tells her to marry and so she does promise her dad. They fix a marriage for Lathapandi but on the night before her marriage, she decides to run away with Bosepandi. When running away at night, they see Sivanandi and he tells them to run away and gives them some money so that they never come back. Sivanandi wants Bosepandi and Lathapandi to run away because he doesn't want Lathapandi to marry the guy he has chosen for her and he can't stop her marriage because he has too much respect in his village. He watches them get married and then he walks home with blood on his shirt (the blood is of a goat that he killed) and lies to everyone that he killed his daughter because of his reputation. Bosepandi and Lathapandi return though and ruin Sivanandi's plans and Bosepandi stated that he returned because his father offered him more money. The film ends with Sivanandi and Bosepandi laughing happily.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sivakarthikeyan]] as Bosepandi M.A M.Phil, President of Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n* [[Sathyaraj]] as Sivanaandi, Bosepandi's rival\n* [[Sri Divya]] as Lathapandi, Bosepandi's love interest\n* [[Soori (actor)|Soori]] as Kodi, Bosepandi's friend and Secretary of Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n* [[Soundararaja]] as Pullichathanni, Sangam member\n* Shalu Shammu as Kodi's lover, Lathapandi's friend\n* [[Rajendran]] as Coolmayi, Sivanandi's enemy and Bosepandi's uncle\n* [[Sriranjini (Tamil actress)|Sriranjini]] as Dhanalakshmi, Lathapandi's mother\n* [[Swaminathan]] as Lawyer Veerasamy, advocate of Sangam \n* [[Elango Kumaravel]] as constable\n* [[Yaar Kannan]] as Bosepandi's father\n* [[Dhandapani]] as Sivanandi's sidekick\n* Subramaniyapuram Raja as Sivanandi's sidekick\n* Hello Kanthaswamy as Sivanandi's sidekick\n* [[Vinodhini Vaidyanathan]] as Inspector Bharathi\n* [[Joe Malloori]] as Police Inspector\n* [[Bindu Madhavi]] as Kalyani (Special Appearance)\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| longtype   = to Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n| artist     = [[D. Imman]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Front cover\n| released   = 2013\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     =\n| language   = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label      = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer   = D. Imman\n| prev_title = [[Desingu Raja]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Pandiya Naadu]]\n| next_year  = 2013\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[D. Imman]], which is the second time he has contributed the score for a film starring [[Sivakarthikeyan]] after ''[[Manam Kothi Paravai]]''. Sivakarthikeyan had sung a song in this film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-10/sivakarthikeyans-new-avatar-sivakarthikeyan-varutha-padatha-valibar-sangam-26-06-13.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan's new avatar |work=Behindwoods |date=26 June 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> The audio was released on 14 July,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/95328.html |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam audio launch on July 14 |work=Indiaglitz |date=10 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> Actor [[Dhanush]] released the audio CD and director [[A. R. Murugadoss]] received it. ''Behindwoods'' wrote:\"Made for onscreen enjoyment\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-songs-review.html |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam Songs Review |work=Behindwoods |date=14 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> while Indiaglitz wrote:\"Overall one for the mass and fun factor\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/musicreview/17659.html |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam Music Review songs lyrics |work=Indiaglitz |date=18 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n{{track listing\n| headline = Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| all_lyrics = [[Yugabharathi]]\n| lyrics =\n| title1     = Oodha Colour Ribbon\n| extra1     = Hariharasudan\n\n| title2     = Indha Ponnungale\n| extra2     = Jayamoorthy\n\n| title3     = Paarkathe Paarkathe\n| extra3     = [[Vijay Yesudas]], [[Pooja Vaidyanath]]\n\n| title4     = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n| extra4     = [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Anthony Daasan|Anthony Dasan]]\n\n| title5     = Yennada Yennada\n| extra5     = [[Shreya Ghoshal]], [[Sooraj Santhosh]], [[SuVi]]\n\n| title6     = Indha Ponnungale (Dubstep mix)\n| extra6     = Jayamoorthy, Tha Prophecy\n|length1 = 04:42|length2 = 04:32|length3 = 04:35|length4 = 04:00|length5 = 04:18|length6 = 03:41|total_length = 25:48}}\n\n==Release==\nOn 13 July a making of song recording video of the song sung by [[Sivakarthikeyan]] was released<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HuSxftQY43I|title=YouTube |work=YouTube |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> and next day a theatrical film trailer was released, by Sony Music India on their YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ky4Yy8_KbZs |title=Varuthapadatha Vaalibar Sangam - Official Theatrical Trailer |work=YouTube |date=14 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> The film was given a \"U\" certificate by the [[Central Board of Film Certification|Central Board]]{{Citation needed|date=April 2015}}. The film was released in 340+ screens worldwide, the widest release for Sivakarthikeyan till then.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/preview/17659.html |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam Tamil Movie |work=IndiaGlitz |date=3 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref> The satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Kalaignar TV|Kalaignar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indreporter.com/2014/10/13/deepavali-2014-special-movie-varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-in-kalaignar-tv-channel-on-221014-kalaignar-tv-channel-special-program-on-diwali-2014/ |title=DEEPAVALI 2014 SPECIAL MOVIE VARUTHAPADATHA VALIBAR SANGAM IN KALAIGNAR TV CHANNEL ON 22/10/14, KALAIGNAR TV CHANNEL SPECIAL PROGRAM ON DIWALI 2014 |publisher=Indreporter |date=13 October 2014 |accessdate=5 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n[[Baradwaj Rangan]] wrote, \"The film has enough silliness to qualify as mild amusement, especially in the scenes with Bosepandi and his friend Kodi (Soori) \u2014 but these gags would work just as well as a compilation clip on YouTube. The plotting is too loose to warrant a two-hour-and-forty-minute movie, with sentimental detours and meandering subplots\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Baradwaj Rangan |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-jest-cause/article5104079.ece |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam: Jest cause |work=The Hindu |date=7 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nBehindwoods Review Board rated 2.75 out of 5 and wrote, \"Charmingly mischievous Siva Karthikeyan, comical Soori and the majestic Sathyaraj make VVS a jolly good entertainer.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-review.html |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam Movie Review Sivakarthikeyan, Varutha Padadha Vaalibar Sangam |work=Behindwoods |date=6 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nPraising the work of the actors in the film, Indiaglitz says, \"The film's biggest strength is Sathyaraj, and the climax alone is enough to show his strength. The man who has shifted gears towards character roles is doing a good job out of it. Siva again, it is a wonder to see this guy in yet another healthy fun movie.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/17659.html |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam Tamil Movie Review |work=IndiaGlitz |date=6 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[Rediff]] wrote, \"Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam is boring and gets repetitive after a while\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-south-varthapadatha-valibar-sangam-is-boring/20130909.htm |title=Review: Varthapadatha Valibar Sangam is boring|work=Rediff|date=9 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nSandesh of Oneindia says, \" 'Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam' is a full-ledged comedy and family entertainer. Actor Sivakarthikeyan, Sathyaraj and comedian Parota Soori are the main highlight of the movie.\"\n\nAccording to Sify, \"''[[Ponram]]'' through VVS follows the comedy template set by his guru Rajesh and blends them with his hero Sivakarthikeyan's image. Add D Imman's peppy melodies with a rural touch and you get a mass comedy entertainer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-review-tamil-15037957.html |title=Movie Review : Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam|publisher=Sify|accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n\"IBNLive has given 3 out of 5 \"you are likely to enjoy it more\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-review-this-tamil-film-entertains/420249-71-178.html |title=IBNLive |publisher=IBNLive |accessdate=7 September 2013}}</ref> IBTimes review verdict is \"Good Entertainer, Worth a Watch\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/504356/20130907/varuthapadadha-valibar-sangam-review-roundup-sivakarthikeyan-vvs.htm |title=IBTimes |work=IBTimes |accessdate=7 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[The New Indian Express]] wrote, \"A promising work by a debutant, the film though not the best of comedies, makes for a fairly pleasant watch\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Mannath |first=Malini |url=http://newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/Varuthapadatha-Vaalibar-Sangam-Karthikeyans-splendid-take/2013/09/08/article1773669.ece |title=Varuthapadatha Vaalibar Sangam: Karthikeyan's splendid take |work=The New Indian Express |date=8 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Box office==\n''Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam'' had the biggest opening in Sivakarthikeyan's career at the time of its release;<ref>{{cite web|title='Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam' opens big!|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-opens-big-news-tamil-njimS5fbeee.html |work=SIFY|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref> it earned approximately {{INR}}3.55&nbsp;crore net on its first day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/504464/20130908/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-box-office-collection-vvs.htm |title=IBTimes |work=IBTimes |accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref> According to Sify, the film, which released in 343 screens in Tamil Nadu, took {{INR}} 3.25 Cr in its first three days and had collected {{INR}} 11.5 Cr after 17 days at the Tamil Nadu box office.<ref name=\"sifyvvs\"/>\n\nThe film was considered financially successful.<ref name=\"sifyvvs\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam box office collection|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-box-office-oct-13.html|work=Behindwoods|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3215258}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Tiruchirappalli]]\n[[Category:Tamil films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Directorial debut films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by D. Imman]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2013 film directed by Ponram}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam,\n| image          = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam Poster.jpg\n| caption        = Promotional poster\n| director       = [[Ponram]]\n| producer       = P. Madhan\n| writer         = Ponram [[M. Rajesh]] (dialogues)\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Sivakarthikeyan]]|[[Sathyaraj]]|[[Sri Divya]]|[[Soori (actor)|Soori]]|[[Soundararaja]]}}\n| cinematography = [[Balasubramaniem]]\n| editing        = [[Vivek Harshan]]\n| studio         = [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]]\n| distributor    = Escape Artists Motion Pictures, Khafa Exports (Overseas)\n| released       = {{Film date|2013|09|06|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 158 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| music          = [[D. Imman]]\n| budget         = {{INR}}7.1 crore<ref name=\"sifyvvs\">{{cite web|title=VVS is a blockbuster - The Economics|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vvs-is-a-blockbuster-the-economics-news-tamil-njzj7ugafij.html|work=SIFY|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref>\n| gross          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n'''''Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam''''' ({{trans|The Association of Carefree Youths}}) is a 2013 [[India]]n [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[romantic comedy]] film directed by ''[[Ponram]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/audio-beat-varuthapadatha-vaalibar-sangam-songs-to-lift-your-mood/article4959791.ece |title=Audio Beat: Varuthapadatha Vaalibar Sangam \u2013 Songs to lift your mood |last=S. R. Ashok Kumar |date=27 July 2013 |website=The Hindu |access-date=16 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Varutha-Padatha-Valibar-Sangam-first-look-poster/articleshow/20551411.cms |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam first look poster |work=The Times of India |date=12 June 2013 |accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref> It stars [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Sathyaraj]] and [[Sri Divya]].<ref name=\"sifyvvs1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-gets-ready-news-tamil-ngnk5qdjieg.html |title='Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam' gets ready!|work=Sify|accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-02/news-interviews/38216767_1_sivakarthikeyan-siva-karthikeyan-sathyaraj |title=Sivakarthikeyan and Sathyraj join hands! |work=The Times of India |date=2 April 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> The film was produced by [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]] and has music by [[D. Imman]]. Rajesh wrote the dialogues for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-12-28/news-interviews/36035579_1_siva-karthikeyan-imman-manam-kothi-paravai |title=Imman composes for Siva Karthikeyan's next |work=The Times of India |date=28 December 2012 |accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref> It was filmed in [[Padalur]], [[Theni]], [[Tiruchi]] and [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"sifyvvs1\" /> The film released on 6 September 2013 and performed well at the box office.<ref name=\"Sify top 5\">{{cite web|title=Chennai Box-Office \u2013 Sep 13 to 15|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boxoffice.php?id=15038902&cid=13525926|work=SIFY|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref> The film was remade in Kannada as ''[[Adyaksha]]'' with Sharan playing the lead role and in Telugu as ''[[Current Theega]]'' with [[Manoj Manchu]].<ref>http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/reviews/Movie-review-Sharan-Adyaksha/articleshow/40310678.cms</ref><ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Current-Teega-is-a-Tamil-film-remake/articleshow/42641729.cms</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThe film begins with police arriving at Sivanandi's ([[Sathyaraj]]) house questioning him about killing his daughter Lathapandi ([[Sri Divya]]) because she ran away with the guy she loved. Bosepandi ([[Sivakarthikeyan]]) and Kodi ([[Soori (actor)|Soori]]) are two friends who are the leaders of a group called Varuthapadadha Valibar Sangam. One day, Bosepandi falls in love with Kalyani ([[Bindu Madhavi]]) who is a teacher at a school. Bosepandi writes a love letter for her but wants someone to go give it to her so that's when he finds Lathapandi. Lathapandi gives the letter to her teacher and tricks Bosepandi into believing many things.\n\nSivanandi fixes a marriage for Lathapandi but she is not willing to marry because she is very young and she wants to study further. Despite her attempts, nothing stops her marriage. Her marriage was posted on a billboard and Bosepandi and Kodi decide to stop it. They go to the police station and threaten the police that they will go to the commissioner. The police talks to Sivanandi and makes him stop the marriage. One day, Lathapandi delivers the news to Bosepandi that Kalyani is getting married. He decides to move on in life, so he arranges for a Dindigul programme to happen in his area. He sees Lathapandi in a sari and immediately falls in love with her. The same night, the police reveals to Sivanandi that the person who stopped Lathapandi's marriage was Bosepandi.\n\nA day later he tells her about his love for her but she ignores him and says no. Bosepandi walks away listening to a sad song when a gang comes and bashes him. He later finds out that it was Sivanandi's gang who hit him. So Bosepandi and Kodi decide to steal what Sivanandi considers his 'soul' and that is his gun. Bosepandi and Kodi steal the gun and run away and cause a lot of trouble. Bosepandi then tells Lathapandi that he will return the gun if she comes to their friends marriage and so he returns the gun without anyone knowing. Lathapandi in return, goes to that marriage and takes lots of photos with Bosepandi. Her mother warns her that this is not correct and she should stop it. Sivanandi's cow falls into a well when he goes out of town so Bosepandi helps to get it out. That night he stays with Lathapandi in her house and they see Sivanandi sleepwalking. After that, they wake up in the morning and they see Sivanandi walking again. This time he is awake but Bosepandi thinks he's sleepwalking again and so he tells Sivanandi about liking his daughter. Once he finds out that he is indeed awake, he runs out of that house.\n\nSivanandi then makes Lathapandi promise that she will only marry the guy who Sivanandi tells her to marry and so she does promise her dad. They fix a marriage for Lathapandi but on the night before her marriage, she decides to run away with Bosepandi. When running away at night, they see Sivanandi and he tells them to run away and gives them some money so that they never come back. Sivanandi wants Bosepandi and Lathapandi to run away because he doesn't want Lathapandi to marry the guy he has chosen for her and he can't stop her marriage because he has too much respect in his village. He watches them get married and then he walks home with blood on his shirt (the blood is of a goat that he killed) and lies to everyone that he killed his daughter because of his reputation. Bosepandi and Lathapandi return though and ruin Sivanandi's plans and Bosepandi stated that he returned because his father offered him more money. The film ends with Sivanandi and Bosepandi laughing happily.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sivakarthikeyan]] as Bosepandi M.A M.Phil, President of Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n* [[Sathyaraj]] as Sivanaandi, Bosepandi's rival\n* [[Sri Divya]] as Lathapandi, Bosepandi's love interest\n* [[Soori (actor)|Soori]] as Kodi, Bosepandi's friend and Secretary of Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n* [[Soundararaja]] as Pullichathanni, Sangam member\n* Shalu Shammu as Kodi's lover, Lathapandi's friend\n* [[Rajendran]] as Coolmayi, Sivanandi's enemy and Bosepandi's uncle\n* [[Sriranjini (Tamil actress)|Sriranjini]] as Dhanalakshmi, Lathapandi's mother\n* [[Swaminathan]] as Lawyer Veerasamy, advocate of Sangam \n* [[Elango Kumaravel]] as constable\n* [[Yaar Kannan]] as Bosepandi's father\n* [[Dhandapani]] as Sivanandi's sidekick\n* Subramaniyapuram Raja as Sivanandi's sidekick\n* Hello Kanthaswamy as Sivanandi's sidekick\n* [[Vinodhini Vaidyanathan]] as Inspector Bharathi\n* [[Joe Malloori]] as Police Inspector\n* [[Bindu Madhavi]] as Kalyani (Special Appearance)\n{{colend}}\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| longtype   = to Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n| artist     = [[D. Imman]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Front cover\n| released   = 2013\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     =\n| language   = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label      = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer   = D. Imman\n| prev_title = [[Desingu Raja]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Pandiya Naadu]]\n| next_year  = 2013\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[D. Imman]], which is the second time he has contributed the score for a film starring [[Sivakarthikeyan]] after ''[[Manam Kothi Paravai]]''. Sivakarthikeyan had sung a song in this film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-10/sivakarthikeyans-new-avatar-sivakarthikeyan-varutha-padatha-valibar-sangam-26-06-13.html |title=Sivakarthikeyan's new avatar |work=Behindwoods |date=26 June 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> The audio was released on 14 July,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/95328.html |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam audio launch on July 14 |work=Indiaglitz |date=10 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> Actor [[Dhanush]] released the audio CD and director [[A. R. Murugadoss]] received it. ''Behindwoods'' wrote:\"Made for onscreen enjoyment\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-songs-review.html |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam Songs Review |work=Behindwoods |date=14 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> while Indiaglitz wrote:\"Overall one for the mass and fun factor\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/musicreview/17659.html |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam Music Review songs lyrics |work=Indiaglitz |date=18 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n{{track listing\n| headline = Track list\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| all_lyrics = [[Yugabharathi]]\n| lyrics =\n| title1     = Oodha Colour Ribbon\n| extra1     = Hariharasudan\n\n| title2     = Indha Ponnungale\n| extra2     = Jayamoorthy\n\n| title3     = Paarkathe Paarkathe\n| extra3     = [[Vijay Yesudas]], [[Pooja Vaidyanath]]\n\n| title4     = Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam\n| extra4     = [[Sivakarthikeyan]], [[Anthony Daasan|Anthony Dasan]]\n\n| title5     = Yennada Yennada\n| extra5     = [[Shreya Ghoshal]], [[Sooraj Santhosh]], [[SuVi]]\n\n| title6     = Indha Ponnungale (Dubstep mix)\n| extra6     = Jayamoorthy, Tha Prophecy\n|length1 = 04:42|length2 = 04:32|length3 = 04:35|length4 = 04:00|length5 = 04:18|length6 = 03:41|total_length = 25:48}}\n\n==Release==\nOn 13 July a making of song recording video of the song sung by [[Sivakarthikeyan]] was released<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HuSxftQY43I|title=YouTube |work=YouTube |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> and next day a theatrical film trailer was released, by Sony Music India on their YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ky4Yy8_KbZs |title=Varuthapadatha Vaalibar Sangam - Official Theatrical Trailer |work=YouTube |date=14 July 2013 |accessdate=16 August 2013}}</ref> The film was given a \"U\" certificate by the [[Central Board of Film Certification|Central Board]]{{Citation needed|date=April 2015}}. The film was released in 340+ screens worldwide, the widest release for Sivakarthikeyan till then.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/preview/17659.html |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam Tamil Movie |work=IndiaGlitz |date=3 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref> The satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Kalaignar TV|Kalaignar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indreporter.com/2014/10/13/deepavali-2014-special-movie-varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-in-kalaignar-tv-channel-on-221014-kalaignar-tv-channel-special-program-on-diwali-2014/ |title=DEEPAVALI 2014 SPECIAL MOVIE VARUTHAPADATHA VALIBAR SANGAM IN KALAIGNAR TV CHANNEL ON 22/10/14, KALAIGNAR TV CHANNEL SPECIAL PROGRAM ON DIWALI 2014 |publisher=Indreporter |date=13 October 2014 |accessdate=5 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n[[Baradwaj Rangan]] wrote, \"The film has enough silliness to qualify as mild amusement, especially in the scenes with Bosepandi and his friend Kodi (Soori) \u2014 but these gags would work just as well as a compilation clip on YouTube. The plotting is too loose to warrant a two-hour-and-forty-minute movie, with sentimental detours and meandering subplots\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Baradwaj Rangan |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-jest-cause/article5104079.ece |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam: Jest cause |work=The Hindu |date=7 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nBehindwoods Review Board rated 2.75 out of 5 and wrote, \"Charmingly mischievous Siva Karthikeyan, comical Soori and the majestic Sathyaraj make VVS a jolly good entertainer.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-review.html |title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam Movie Review Sivakarthikeyan, Varutha Padadha Vaalibar Sangam |work=Behindwoods |date=6 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nPraising the work of the actors in the film, Indiaglitz says, \"The film's biggest strength is Sathyaraj, and the climax alone is enough to show his strength. The man who has shifted gears towards character roles is doing a good job out of it. Siva again, it is a wonder to see this guy in yet another healthy fun movie.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/17659.html |title=Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam Tamil Movie Review |work=IndiaGlitz |date=6 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[Rediff]] wrote, \"Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam is boring and gets repetitive after a while\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-south-varthapadatha-valibar-sangam-is-boring/20130909.htm |title=Review: Varthapadatha Valibar Sangam is boring|work=Rediff|date=9 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nSandesh of Oneindia says, \" 'Varutha Padatha Valibar Sangam' is a full-ledged comedy and family entertainer. Actor Sivakarthikeyan, Sathyaraj and comedian Parota Soori are the main highlight of the movie.\"\n\nAccording to Sify, \"''[[Ponram]]'' through VVS follows the comedy template set by his guru Rajesh and blends them with his hero Sivakarthikeyan's image. Add D Imman's peppy melodies with a rural touch and you get a mass comedy entertainer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-review-tamil-15037957.html |title=Movie Review : Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam|publisher=Sify|accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n\"IBNLive has given 3 out of 5 \"you are likely to enjoy it more\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-review-this-tamil-film-entertains/420249-71-178.html |title=IBNLive |publisher=IBNLive |accessdate=7 September 2013}}</ref> IBTimes review verdict is \"Good Entertainer, Worth a Watch\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/504356/20130907/varuthapadadha-valibar-sangam-review-roundup-sivakarthikeyan-vvs.htm |title=IBTimes |work=IBTimes |accessdate=7 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[The New Indian Express]] wrote, \"A promising work by a debutant, the film though not the best of comedies, makes for a fairly pleasant watch\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Mannath |first=Malini |url=http://newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/Varuthapadatha-Vaalibar-Sangam-Karthikeyans-splendid-take/2013/09/08/article1773669.ece |title=Varuthapadatha Vaalibar Sangam: Karthikeyan's splendid take |work=The New Indian Express |date=8 September 2013 |accessdate=17 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Box office==\n''Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam'' had the biggest opening in Sivakarthikeyan's career at the time of its release;<ref>{{cite web|title='Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam' opens big!|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-opens-big-news-tamil-njimS5fbeee.html |work=SIFY|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref> it earned approximately {{INR}}3.55&nbsp;crore net on its first day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/504464/20130908/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-box-office-collection-vvs.htm |title=IBTimes |work=IBTimes |accessdate=8 September 2013}}</ref> According to Sify, the film, which released in 343 screens in Tamil Nadu, took {{INR}} 3.25 Cr in its first three days and had collected {{INR}} 11.5 Cr after 17 days at the Tamil Nadu box office.<ref name=\"sifyvvs\"/>\n\nThe film was considered financially sucessful.<ref name=\"sifyvvs\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Varuthapadatha Valibar Sangam box office collection|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam/varuthapadatha-valibar-sangam-box-office-oct-13.html|work=Behindwoods|accessdate=23 December 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3215258}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\